      "text": "I can see these are text message screenshots showing what appears to be work-related conversations with someone named Mike La. I need to extract the work schedule information from the messages to calculate hours.\n\nLooking through the images:\n\nImage 1:\n- Shows a conversation about plumbing supplies from Hirsch Pipe & Supply\n- There's a message about \"July 30th Wednesday 9am-4pm -30 lunch\"\n- This indicates 7 hours of work (9am to 4pm = 7 hours, minus 30 minutes for lunch = 6.5 hours)\n\nImage 2:\n- Shows a message about \"Parking garage: 8:30am - 4pm (30 minute lunch)\"\n- This indicates 7.5 hours minus 0.5 hours for lunch = 7 hours\n\nImage 3:\n- Shows some Claude AI conversation but also has \"Monday 07/21 8:30am-4:30pm -30min lunch\"\n- This indicates 8 hours minus 0.5 hours = 7.5 hours\n\nImage 4:\n- Shows \"Tuesday July 22 9-4pm -30 lunch\"\n- This indicates 7 hours minus 0.5 hours = 6.5 hours\n\nImage 5:\n- Shows \"July 29th Tuesday 9:30am-4:30pm\"\n- This indicates 7 hours (no lunch mentioned, so I'll assume it's included in the time or ask for clarification)\n\nLet me calculate these:\n- July 21 (Monday): 8:30am-4:30pm with 30min lunch = 7.5 hours\n- July 22 (Tuesday): 9am-4pm with 30min lunch = 6.5 hours\n- July 29 (Tuesday): 9:30am-4:30pm = 7 hours (assuming lunch is included or needs clarification)\n- July 30 (Wednesday): 9am-4pm with 30min lunch = 6.5 hours\n \nI'll need to verify the exact date for the parking garage work shift. The details are unclear, so I should seek additional information to confirm the specific day and precise work hours.Looking at your text messages, I can see several work schedule entries. Let me calculate the hours for each day I can identify:\n\n**July 21 (Monday)**: 8:30am-4:30pm with 30min lunch\n- 8 hours total - 0.5 hours lunch = **7.5 hours**\n\n**July 22 (Tuesday)**: 9am-4pm with 30min lunch  \n- 7 hours total - 0.5 hours lunch = **6.5 hours**\n\n**July 29 (Tuesday)**: 9:30am-4:30pm\n- 7 hours total = **7 hours** (no lunch deduction mentioned)\n\n**July 30 (Wednesday)**: 9am-4pm with 30min lunch\n- 7 hours total - 0.5 hours lunch = **6.5 hours**\n\n**Parking garage day**: 8:30am-4pm with 30min lunch\n- 7.5 hours total - 0.5 hours lunch = **7 hours** (need to know which day this was)\n\n**Total so far**: 34.5 hours (if the parking garage was a separate day)\n\nCould you clarify:\n1. Which day was the parking garage work?\n2. For July 29th, was lunch included in that time or should I deduct 30 minutes?\n\nThis will help me give you the most accurate total.",
